57th Evoker of Lanys T'vyl<BR>
<a href=http://www.seven-dreams.org/><i>Seven Dreams</i></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elrond>elrond</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/6/01 9:05:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: People crying over new port spells</span><hr size=1> obviously, people pick wizards for two things: Best DDs and teleports. that was our class description. After the class balance threads and the addition of the two new bain spells, we were told to wait for more changes. Apparantly these are the changes. i would be fine getting these translocates if they were included with a little more balancing post 50 but it seems Verant thinks translocates are balancing us. these translocates only help other classes, since its now so easy to port people, wizards cant refuse anymore. its like casting sow now, no zone, no affect on us. since we cant refuse while dr00ds can, we are going to be the masters of paying 10 bucks a month so we can spend half our time getting bugged for translocates.<br>
<br>
now besides all that, they make these spells drop off mobs. As if we should go out of our way to find these spells that only help others. While i am certain a strike would not work, i understand the reasoning behind it. i also understand that verant wasted our time by making us all beta testers in the balancing thread and then leading us on about changes to come. if there are DD changes in the works,  they should have been resolved before they started even discussing this line of spells.<br>
<br>
i will never again waste my time giving input to verant when they request it. if anything, i feel lied to about &quot;more changes in the works&quot; regarding balancing. its just a game with deceptive instructions. i wont quit but i lost all respect for Absor and all his Verant lil friends. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulenadaynastardew.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lenadayna Stardew</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/6/01 9:11:09 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=c:\windows\desktop\lena.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: People crying over new port spells</span><hr size=1>   Aren't these spells being sold in the Temple of Solusek Ro on Test?<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elrond>elrond</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/6/01 9:40:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: People crying over new port spells</span><hr size=1> well i had read alot of posts about &quot;how much would you pay for translocates&quot; and such. its good to know at least we dont have to work extra hard for these spells. But the rest of my post stands. You guys need to give up on balancing if only to save yourselves from the dissapointment.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aennyilofkarana>Aennyil of Karana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/9/01 3:18:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: People crying over new port spells</span><hr size=1> The four portal specific spells: Tox, Fay, NK and DL are all sold in Sol Ro Temple and are lvl 39 if memory serves.<br>
<br>
Group Trans is lvl 52 and is mob dropped only and is MEANT to be a rare drop. Given how many different zones it's dropped I suggest if your guild wants you to have this you go raid those locales soon before Verant decides to emergency patch and lower the drop rate.<br>
<br>
Me? I don't give a flying fuck* if I get the spell or not. I won't pay more than I payed for the others at a vendor.<br>
<br>
As far as balance goes? At this point I couldn't give a red rectum whether Verant wakes up and cleans house ... (that's what it'd take.) I just wish I could get groups.<br>
<br>
YES I know I can go quad kite ... I play this game to socialize ...<br>
<br>
If I had it to do over, I'd have made a cleric since I REALLY don't mind sitting on my ass after buffing people till the effluvia hits the fan.<br>
<br>
*pls forgive my language but I'm angered <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www,kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/10/01 8:56:31 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimtoo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: People crying over new port spells</span><hr size=1> I just don't understand all this venom about getting new spells.  How can you be so pissed off Verant is adding things to the class?  I LIKE the translocates, I just am baffled.  Sure, they should do more for Wizards in a hundred other ways but I'll NEVER begrudge Verant for doing something for a class. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aennyilofkarana>Aennyil of Karana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/10/01 9:27:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: People crying over new port spells</span><hr size=1> My venom is not at these spells per se, but that Verant has as yet done nothing for us as a class to make us more desirable in groups. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/useverinewolfe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Severine Wolfe</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/10/01 3:12:03 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.clan-donald.com/screenshots/severine.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: People crying over new port spells</span><hr size=1> Grim you ask about the venom in the rants lately.  I think I can cast a little light on that.<br>
<br>
When my husband started playing EQ in Phase 3 Beta he played a wizard. Wizards rocked then.  When I started playing last year (finally) I chose to be a wizard based on the Wizard Vision in Beta... I hadn't noticed that it had totally changed and never asked my husband why he played at Shaman through 52 levels instead of sticking with his wizzie.<br>
<br>
I love my wizard.  I am proud of what she has done and what she is capable of doing, however Verant has belittled wizards to the level of CAB DRIVERS!  If I can send people through space by arcanely manipulating it, why can I not there for summon someone?  Why do mages get CoH and we dont, if we are indeed the Masters of Arcane Transportation?<br>
<br>
Why?  Because Verant doesn't care.  They don't have to. <p>Severine <BR>
High Elf Wizard<BR>
Thank you for flying Air Severine and remember, your seat cushion may be used as a flotation device<BR>
:)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www,kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/10/01 9:14:04 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimtoo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: People crying over new port spells</span><hr size=1> I'm the last person you have to convince that Verant needs to look at damage and at all levels of Wizards.  Believe me I have that one down like Clinton does lies.  The problem is, people are acting like Translocates are a sign of the apocalypse and screaming about how awful they are.  These are nice new spells, they are damn convenient for Wizards and other classes, its a big benefit to the entire game.<br>
<br>
We gotta separate the issues a little.  Should Verant examine our damage from level 1 to 60?  Absolutely, without any argument from me nor doubt.  Is getting teleports a slap in the face?  Only if they ignore damage and only if they somehow hurt the class.  They don't hurt us, they help us, people LIKE Wizards more.  They might not care if we group with them any more than yesterday (and they don't) but I get even more respect and politeness from people than ever now that I can translocate folks around.  Its the Cleric Res effect, don't piss off the Wizard, they are your ride outta town at the end of the day. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/useverinewolfe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Severine Wolfe</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/11/01 3:47:53 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.clan-donald.com/screenshots/severine.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: People crying over new port spells</span><hr size=1> &gt;<br>
<br>
What will they do if we refuse to be that ride? <p>Severine <BR>
High Elf Wizard<BR>
Thank you for flying Air Severine and remember, your seat cushion may be used as a flotation device<BR>
:)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://keith.vaughan.home.mindspring.com/img/ball3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/11/01 5:28:09 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Anger....</span><hr size=1> I think I am more angry now than I was when I first heard the idea.  The number of times I get bothered has definitely escalated.  No I don't think this the apocolypse.  I also don't overly mind the spells.  I guess I'm mostly angry at the communication.  Verant has been a lot less verbal about situations regarding our class.  Except for the word &quot;NO!&quot;  I have no problem remaining calm.  I can rant calmly and rationally.  I still believe these spells are a bone that we've been thrown.  However, I am totally open minded to being wrong.  Sitting and waiting...<br>
<br>
W.F. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utoyoda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Toyoda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/11/01 8:58:25 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.wirebooktech.com/desolatecry/toy2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: People crying over new port spells</span><hr size=1> when all else fails, drink away your problems.<br>
